  "label": "The Filament Alcove",
  "description": "The Filament Alcove is a compact sleeping chamber cut into the glass-dark composite behind the cantina’s sound-baffled panels, its surfaces scored with the Anchorage’s repeating cell-grids. Radiant strands set into rectilinear ceiling channels provide hard-edged, metered illumination that divides the space into strict intervals. A wall-berth of matte latticework folds flush when stowed, leaving a narrow floor lane aligned to the cantina’s axial geometry. A single mooring-view slit, precision-framed and glare-damped, admits a disciplined slice of the void-channels beyond.",
